   Latest News

   This page was last updated on: Thursday, 20 December, 2001

   Effective December 17, 2001, the United States Bankruptcy Court -
   District of New Hampshire will migrage to a new browser-based case
   management system. Users will need an Internet service provider to
   access Pacer information.  The URL is http://ecf.nhb.uscourts.gov. Your
   present PACER login and password will remain the same. As a courtesy to
   modem users, we will keep the old PACER system available until the end
   of the year with information current through 12/12/01.  If you have any
   questions, please contact the courts automation department at (603)
   222-2620-(3).

   Notice regarding public access to bankruptcy case information.

   ATTENTION ATTORNEYS AND SUPPORT STAFF: Please visit the training page
   in the CM/ECF section.  There you will find attorney cbts (computer
   based training) modules with respect to CM/ECF.  Please give them a
   try.

   Click here to view the notice of amendment to official bankruptcy
   forms. Obtain amended forms from the Bankruptcy Schedules page

   Judge Deasy is making available a copy of materials that he and Jeffrey
   A. Schreiber prepared for the 2001 ABI Northeast Bankruptcy Conference
   held July 12-15, 2001 entitled Chapter 13 Under the New Bankruptcy
   Bill. Judge Deasy is also making available a copy of a handout he
   prepared for the seminar entitled Constitutionality of the Means Test.

   Effective July 1, 2001 there has been an increase in certain fees and a
   change for the fee for obtaining electronic records.  Please click here
   to view the new fee schedule or go to the to Filing and Fee page and
   click on Court Filing Fee Schedule.

   Administrative Order AO 2090-2 regarding Disciplilnary Rules and
   Procedures was updated on 2/2/01. That updated version is now available
   in the Administraitve Orders link on the Forms and Rules page

   The United States Bankruptcy Court will honor additional credit cards
   effective immediately. Heretofore, the court was able to accept only
   Mastercard and Visa. In connection with its future electronic case
   filing system, the court will now accept American Express, Discover,
   and Diners Club

   Please be advised that the Court has issued a new Administrative Order
   1050-01 regarding Citation Format for Opinions Issued by This Court.

   Please be advised that on April 1, 2001, automatic adjustments to the
   dollar amounts stated in various provisions of the Bankruptcy Code
   became effective.  These amended dollar amounts apply to cases filed on
   or after April 1, 2001. Please click here to see the adjustments.

   Please be advised that Schedule E and the Proof of Claim form were
   amended April 1, 2001 to reflect the adjusted dollar amounts. These
   forms will apply to cases filed on or after that date.

